The forces of the giant strike are gathering
The League Trade Unions and the National Federation of Workers' Commissions will set up a strike commission on Friday to coordinate Monday's strike that will last for an indefinite period.
A protest rally will be held on Saturday, while on Monday - the day on which the final vote on the public health law will be held - will begin work.
This action will surely cause major transport difficulties, as rail traffic will be stopped completely and until 1 p.m. the workers of the Budapest Collective Transport Company will also be on strike.
On Friday afternoon, the League Trade Unions will report on the details of their strike on Monday that they will hold in conjunction with the National Federation of Workers' Commissions.
The strike commission of the LIGA and the National Union of Machinists will also be set up to coordinate Monday's actions.
A protest rally will be held on Saturday, while on Monday the participating unions will go on strike indefinitely, if no agreement is reached with the government.
This means that - on the day of the parliamentary vote on the public health law - they did not report on the date of the end of the strike.
If the National Assembly disapproves of the public health law, the unions will immediately withdraw their call for strike action.
Instead, if the law is passed, strike committees will meet and decide on the future.
Based on Monday's agenda of the National Assembly, it is also possible that a vote on the public health law will only be voted on in the very early hours of the night, or at best near midnight.
As a result of the strike that will begin on Monday, there will be significant difficulties in transport: on the railways it will stop working indefinitely, on the morning a part of Budapest's collective transport and more than half of the intercity bus transport of the Volán companies will stop.
Simultaneously, in many parts of the country there will be closure of half of the roads.
Many trade unions and civil organizations have joined the strike, their names are constantly updated on the League's website.
Some unions announced their strike indefinitely, others for a definite time.
Until Thursday afternoon, the State Railway and the Free Railway Workers Union (SLTF) were unable to reach an agreement even on the minimum services, although, as the Christmas holidays approach, more and more people travel on the trains are approaching.
According to information received so far, from the beginning of the day until 1 p.m. will be on strike, the workers of the Budapest Collective Transport Company, those of Budapest Airport from 7 to 9 a.m. on the morning, will hold a four-hour strike from the LIGA of the Electrical Industry and Thermal Energy, the Educator Unions called for a strike of 2 and the Democratic Union of Educators from 2 to 8 hours.
The Hungarian Association of Physicians will act on a national strike at alternative times and the Democratic Union of Health and Social Workers (SDTSSS), which are part of the Forum for Trade Union Cooperation, will hold a two-hour warning strike.
The most important of the four demands made by the League is for the government to withdraw its proposal for public health reform and subject a new conception to a social debate.
The second demand is that they gradually introduce the new form of pension calculation that will come into force next year.
The third is that they ensure, even before 2010, in the case of advanced pensions the possibility that the occupations that deserve it can enter the system.
The fourth reason for the strike is that the Free Trade Union of Railway Workers (SLTF) which is part of the League Trade Unions, does not accept the proposal of the Ministry of Economy and Transport on the railway side lines and expects another different proposal.
Political Capital: Risk Increases in the Country by the Hungarian Guard
According to the Risk Analysis Division (Risk Analysing Division) of the Political Capital, the activity of the Hungarian Guard, constituted in August of this year with the support of the Better Hungary Movement, from several points of view the political risk of Hungary and the region has increased.
The "risk warning" of the company is written: in relation to the activity of the Hungarian Guard the greatest political risk is the fact that "with the aggravation of ethnic tensions between the gypsy and non-gypsy population of Hungary, even in the short term violent ethnic clashes may occur."
The main reason for this is that the political strategy of the Hungarian Guard is probably the provocation of an event of this character - added the representative of the research institute.
They stated that all this is due to one of the main faults of the protagonists of Hungarian political life: "the protagonists of public life gave the public debate on the gypsy problem to the representatives of radical and extremist political groups, who were able to base their political strategy on the discrepancies between Gypsies and Hungarians."
This exacerbates the problem, makes normal dialogue impossible, strengthens extremists and increases the likelihood of the outbreak of violent conflict - they estimate.
In addition, according to the research institute, the activity of the National Guard, as a result of the great attention of the national and international average, "significantly deteriorated the image of Hungary abroad, especially with regard to the stability and democratic development of the country."
