The party isn't always written with red numbers
In Hungary the law precisely defines the days that are written with red numbers in the calendar and has already become a widespread practice that around the holidays - that the next year will be less - the working days are reorganized.
Even in the EU or in North America, the holidays are not united.
Hungarian laws make a difference between national holiday, state holiday and holidays.
The festive days are mainly related to religious feasts and historical ephemerides.
Let's celebrate the New Year too: both the last day of the old year, and the first day of the new year is festive - the latter above all so that those who spent having spent celebrating the old year can rest.
Throughout the year we have eleven parties written with red numbers on the calendar.
It is a national holiday on March 15 in memory of the revolution of 1848 and October 23, a day commemorating the 1956 revolution.
On August 20, we celebrated the founding of the State, on May 1st of the work party, on 1 and 2 November we remember our deceased relatives and friends.
In addition, in our country, the Easter of Resurrection, Pentecost and Christmas are two-day feasts.
According to the calendar, our state, national or religious holidays rarely coincide with a weekend, so it is often bridged when before or after the party there is only one working day.
In exchange for weekends elongated like this, on previous Saturdays you cannot be absent from work or school.
He is the Minister of Labour who regulates in his specific decree when we have to work exactly in exchange for the day directly preceding or after the party.
This legal rule is mandatory for all employers and their employees, as well as for employees and public officials.
It is not mandatory for companies and service institutions that, due to their role, work uninterruptedly even during the festive days.
This year the order of work can be altered only around the festivals of the end of the year: from December 24 life in the country practically stops, since according to the experiences, most people "make bridge" during the days between Christmas and the end of the year or take their vacation during these days.
The next one several of our holidays will coincide with mid-to-weekly, so there will be fewer changes in working days than this year.
First the agenda around the work party will be changed so that then, for four successive days, the workers can rest.
Saturday, April 26 will be a working day, so that in return Friday 2 May it will be a holiday.
The other change relates to the feast of October 23: Saturday, October 18, we will have to work instead of Friday 24.
On the other hand, the anus that comes during the end-of-year party can be rested, since from December 24 there will be no work on almost anywhere, even if the last day of the year is a Wednesday.
