Car insurance, which covers the driver in the face of potential claims, is a significant expense that will depend on various factors, such as age, sex, card seniority, marital status, type of vehicle to be secured or using it, among others.
Having the car is just the beginning.
Choosing the right car insurance is even harder than choosing the vehicle model.
First of all, we have to be clear about what we are talking about.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and the insured company.
This commitment is reflected in an insurance contract, which provides that the company receives the value of the agreed premium in exchange for its responsibility for the obligation to pay compensation in the event of a claim.
The premium is the price of insurance, which is established taking into account various factors, such as age, sex, card seniority, marital status, type of vehicle to be secured or use of the vehicle, among others.
Insurers set their prices according to statistics, so that the higher probability of an accident, the higher the fee to be paid.
That is why both those over 25 and women have to pay lower premiums, as statistics show that they have a lower casualty rate due to their prudence.
Also, taking advantage of the counts, companies have concluded that married people tend to have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The use of the vehicle will influence the frequency, and thus the probability of having some kind of mishap.
By increasing the frequency, the odds increase.
There are many variables that insurers take into account when setting the premium price.
That is why the driver must study the situation well to choose that car insurance that best fits his profile.
Here we will present the most significant variables when choosing one or the other type of insurance, so that this, in addition to adapting to the characteristics of the insured, offers a reasonable price.
Young people under 25 years of age find themselves with various disadvantages when hiring insurance at an affordable price, such as the reduced experience in driving and the seniority of the card.
Although the ideal to be well insured is full-risk insurance, there are other cheaper options.
The most cautious drivers can opt for a full risk with franchise, so that they get the coverage of full-risk insurance but at a more feasible price.
This kind of agreement would mean that the customer pays a part of the amount of the accident.
"The part of the amount of the client's sinister will be pre-established according to the value of the premium, which will be higher the lower the amount," says Luis Noguera, head of Spain of First Europe, online insurance mediator.
Another option is extended third-party insurance, so that the customer ensures protection against damage caused to third parties, but not to those caused in his own car.
In addition, it would be covered by theft, fire and vehicle loss.
A tip.
If you are under 25, try to be careful and avoid the casualties as much as possible, as this will have an impact on the bonus, being able to reduce the cost of insurance in the future.
A bonus is a reduction on the base rate held by the company.
Instead, a penalty is a surcharge on that base rate.
"The bonuses and penalties will depend on the company and the benefit of the company.
If the company has had a good year, it will be able to afford to increase the bonuses," Noguera explains.
After the 25-year range, drivers have it easier to hire insurance, as the accident rate is reduced thanks to the accumulated experience.
For this reason, it is best to take a full risk with franchise.
"Normally young people cannot make use of the experience previously acquired when it comes to using an accident, and even at the time of driving," says the director in Spain of the European company, adding that most accidents occur in the second year of driving, once the 'fear of the rookie' has already passed.
However, if the client is married but still has no children it is preferable for him to negotiate full-risk insurance, as long as his economic situation allows him, of course.
For their part, marriages with children are considered by insurers as the public with the lowest accident rate, so the surcharges will be lower.
In this case the best insurance would be one at all risk with a franchise (may be this of 300 euros), or, when a high level of bonus is available, one to third parties extended from the third year of the vehicle's life.
"They're running more relaxed and have a greater purchasing power to afford to take on a larger amount of franchise," says Luis Noguera.
For retirees, full-risk insurance with franchise (being this one of 150 euros), or one to thirds is recommended when you have a high level of bonus.
It must be said that car insurance is important, not only because it covers the driver in the face of possible casualties, but also because it represents an important expense, which is why it is essential to properly study the insurance that suits us best according to our personal situation.
